com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport
Class SourceInfo

java.lang.Object
  com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.SourceInfo

public final class SourceInfo
extends Object

The source information associated with a particular Card.

Throughout its lifetime, source information is subject to validation rules:

  • If particular SourceInfo properties are marked as mandatory in the schema (see Schema.getSourceInfoMandatoryFields()), then they must have non-null values.
The contents of the various properties must conform to the standard XML types defined in "W3C XML Schema Definition Language (XSD) 1.1 Part 2: Datatypes". Specifically:
  • The values returned by getType(), getReference(), and getDescription() must conform to the "string" XML data type (section 3.3.1).
  • The value returned by getDate() must conform to the "dateTime" XML data type (section 3.3.8).

Since:
1.0
